# Battleship — Naval Command

A full-stack Battleship game built with PHP, MySQL, and vanilla JavaScript. Play against a hunt/target AI or go head-to-head with a friend in local 2-player mode. Features persistent player stats, a leaderboard, and a REST API with authenticated test endpoints for automated grading.

**Live Site:** https://lightslategray-dogfish-869967.hostingersite.com

---

## Features

- **vs Computer** — AI opponent using hunt/target strategy (random shots until a hit, then systematically targets adjacent cells)
- **vs Player** — local 2-player with handoff screens to hide boards between turns
- **5-Ship Fleet** — Carrier (5), Battleship (4), Cruiser (3), Submarine (3), Destroyer (2)
- **Ship Placement** — click to place, press R to rotate, or use random placement
- **Persistent Stats** — player records stored in MySQL (wins, losses, total moves, accuracy)
- **Leaderboard** — all-time win/loss record displayed in-game
- **State Recovery** — game state saved to localStorage so refreshing doesn't lose progress
- **REST API** — separate database-backed API with full game lifecycle support
- **Test Mode** — authenticated endpoints for deterministic grading (ship placement, board reveal, game reset, turn control)

