## Project Structure

```
Battleship/
├── index.php           # Main HTML page (game UI)
├── game.php            # Session-based backend (gameplay actions)
├── api.php             # REST API (database-backed, grading support)
├── db.php              # Database connection config
├── script.js           # Client-side game logic & UI
├── styles.css          # Styling (dark naval theme)
├── .htaccess           # URL rewriting for REST routes
├── schema_game.sql     # Game tables (players, games, game_participants)
├── schema_api.sql      # API tables (api_players, api_games, api_ships, etc.)
├── stats.json          # Default stats template
├── ARCHITECTURE.md     # Detailed architecture documentation
└── sounds/             # Audio effects
```

---

## Architecture

The project has two backend layers:

**`game.php`** — powers the browser-based game. Uses `$_SESSION` for in-game state (ship positions, hits/misses, AI targeting queue) and writes final results to the `players`, `games`, and `game_participants` tables on game over.

**`api.php`** — a stateless REST API backed entirely by the `api_*` database tables. Supports the full game lifecycle (create players, create/join games, place ships, fire shots) plus authenticated test mode endpoints for automated grading.

```
Browser ──AJAX──► game.php ──► $_SESSION + MySQL (game tables)

Grader ──HTTP──► api.php ──► MySQL (api_* tables)
```

## AI Strategy

The computer opponent uses a **hunt/target** algorithm:

- **Hunt mode** — fires at random unvisited cells
- **Target mode** — after scoring a hit, queues all adjacent cells (N/S/E/W) and fires at them systematically
- **Reset** — when a ship is sunk, clears the target queue and returns to hunt mode

